## Implementation Details

The Analytics component is integrated following Next.js App Router best practices:

```typescript
// src/app/layout.tsx
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" suppressHydrationWarning>
      <body className={`${inter.variable} font-sans`}>
        <ThemeProvider attribute="class" defaultTheme="dark" enableSystem={false}>
          <div className="noise-overlay" aria-hidden="true" />
          {children}
        </ThemeProvider>
        <Analytics />  {/* ✅ Correctly placed after children */}
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

## Notes
- This is an App Router project using Next.js 14.2.21
- The Analytics component is non-blocking and loads asynchronously
- No environment variables or additional configuration needed for basic setup
- Analytics will automatically track page views when deployed to Vercel
- Local development will not send analytics data (only works in production)

